      <td><img src="../website images/image5.png" width="250" height="444.666667" alt=""/></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>To use the location tracker with an iPhone you will first need to download OwnTracks.&nbsp;</td>
      <td>Once you have downloaded the app and opened it you will be presented with this pop up, when you see this you MUST allow the app to use your location. It is best to select the "Only While Using the App" option.&nbsp;</td>
      <td>After you have clicked an option from the pop up you will be presented with this message from Own Tracks. It explains how the app will work and once you have read this you can then press continue.&nbsp;</td>
      <td>Once you have pressed continue a map will come up showing your location, however the data of your location isnt currently being recorded. To change the settings so your locaton can be tracked you need to press the I in the top left corner.&nbsp;</td>
      <td>You will then be taken to this page there you will then press settings which is located under the status section.&nbsp;</td>
      
    </tr>
  
  </tbody>
</table>
